Józef Poniatowski (ユゼフ・ポニャトフスキ)

A Polish leader, general, minister of war and army chief, who becomes the future Marshal of the French Empire. Cousin of King Stanisław August Poniatowski and the son of Andrzej Poniatowski, he is a strong and faithful to Poland despite its hardship.
